Sentencas: In the present study, the anode-supported micro-tubular solid oxide fuel cells (MT-SOFCs) with an electrolyte thin interlayer were manufactured.
Titulo: Production, performance and cost analysis of anode-supported NiO-YSZ micro-tubular SOFCs

Sentencas: The anode support tubes consisting of 56 wt% nickel oxide and 44 wt% YSZ (8 mol% yttria (Y2O3) stabilized zirconia (ZrO2)) were produced by using the thermo-extrusion method, whereas the electrolyte and cathode layers were manufactured using the dip-coating method.
Titulo: Production, performance and cost analysis of anode-supported NiO-YSZ micro-tubular SOFCs

Sentencas: The half-cells consisting of anode and electrolyte were manufactured by using two different methods.
Titulo: Production, performance and cost analysis of anode-supported NiO-YSZ micro-tubular SOFCs

Sentencas: In the first method, the anode-support tubes were pre-sintered at 1200 degrees C, then covered with the electrolyte layer by using the dip-coating method and then exposed to second sintering at 1400 degrees C.
Titulo: Production, performance and cost analysis of anode-supported NiO-YSZ micro-tubular SOFCs

Sentencas: In the second method, the anode and electrolyte layers were sintered together at 1400 degrees C (co-sintering) in order to produce the half-cells.
Titulo: Production, performance and cost analysis of anode-supported NiO-YSZ micro-tubular SOFCs

Sentencas: The half-cells that were produced and then coated with cathode solutions by using the dip-coating method and the final cells were successfully produced at the end of the sintering at 1150 degrees C.
Titulo: Production, performance and cost analysis of anode-supported NiO-YSZ micro-tubular SOFCs

Sentencas: The porosity and shrinkage percentage values of these MT-SOFCs differed from each other.
Titulo: Production, performance and cost analysis of anode-supported NiO-YSZ micro-tubular SOFCs

Sentencas: The power densities of these cells were tested at 700 degrees C, 750 degrees C, and 800 degrees C by using H-2 gas as fuel and the results of the microstructural and cost analyses were compared.
Titulo: Production, performance and cost analysis of anode-supported NiO-YSZ micro-tubular SOFCs
